data.description: Huge brick 2-flat with duplex down on a 40-foot wide lot, located on a fantastic block in Logan Square! Such a lovely tree-lined street with a curated mix of Victorian frame single-family homes and traditional brick 2-flats, all on oversized lots. The top floor is a 3 bedroom 1 bathroom apartment with updated finishes, generous bedroom sizes, and great natural light. Enjoy the eat-in kitchen with a walk-in pantry and full laundry room. The first floor and basement create a duplex apartment with 5+ bedrooms and 2 bathrooms and good ceiling height. Also nicely updated with newer finishes throughout. Kitchen features stone countertops, stainless steel appliances and an additional island for eating & prep. Outside there is a wonderfully landscaped front and side yard, providing fantastic curb appeal and plenty of space for a vegetable garden and yard. Behind the home is a paved hangout area, including a covered awning from the garage which provides abundant summertime shade. Enjoy BBQs and weather-protected play on this large back patio. 3 car garage and an additional 1 car outdoor parking pad. Excellent location, walking distance to the lovely retail corridor along Wrightwood avenue (Necessary & Sufficient Coffee, Sugarmoon Bakery), the bars and restaurants along Fullerton (Park & Field, Monster Ramen), and a tree-lined walk to the Logan Square Monument and CTA Blue Line.
